---
import DocsLayout from "../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout title="Introduction">
    <article class="docs-content">
        <h1>Documentation</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-400 mb-8">
            Gabay is an advanced agentic AI that bridges the gap between natural
            language chat and professional productivity tools.
        </p>

        <h2 id="installation">Local Installation</h2>
        <p>
            Gabay can be installed as a Python package for local configuration
            and development:
        </p>
        <pre><code>pip install gabay</code></pre>
        <p>Once installed, run the configuration wizard to get started:</p>
        <pre><code>gabay config</code></pre>

        <h2 id="bot-setup">Telegram API Configuration</h2>
        <p>
            Gabay uses a Bot for commands and a Userbot for acting on your
            behalf.
        </p>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <strong>Create a Bot</strong>: Find <strong>@BotFather</strong> on
                Telegram.
                <ul>
                    <li>Type <code>/newbot</code> and follow instructions.</li>
                    <li>Save your <strong>Bot Token</strong>.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Get API Credentials</strong>:
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        Log in to <a
                            href="https://my.telegram.org"
                            target="_blank"
                            class="text-blue-500">my.telegram.org</a
                        >.
                    </li>
                    <li>Go to <strong>API development tools</strong>.</li>
                    <li>
                        Create an application to get your <code>API_ID</code> and
                        <code>API_HASH</code>.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Authenticate</strong>: Your <code>TELEGRAM_PHONE</code> is
                required for the initial Userbot session login.
            </li>
        </ol>

        <h2 id="google-setup">Google Cloud Architecture</h2>
        <p>
            Enable the following APIs in your <a
                href="https://console.cloud.google.com/"
                target="_blank"
                class="text-blue-500">Google Cloud Console</a
            >:
        </p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-6">
            <div
                class="p-4 bg-bg-card border border-border-main rounded-xl text-center"
            >
                <span class="block text-blue-500 font-bold mb-1">Gmail</span>
                <span class="text-xs text-text-muted italic"
                    >Email Management</span
                >
            </div>
            <div
                class="p-4 bg-bg-card border border-border-main rounded-xl text-center"
            >
                <span class="block text-blue-500 font-bold mb-1">Drive</span>
                <span class="text-xs text-text-muted italic"
                    >File Operations</span
                >
            </div>
            <div
                class="p-4 bg-bg-card border border-border-main rounded-xl text-center"
            >
                <span class="block text-blue-500 font-bold mb-1">Docs</span>
                <span class="text-xs text-text-muted italic"
                    >Research Reports</span
                >
            </div>
            <div
                class="p-4 bg-bg-card border border-border-main rounded-xl text-center"
            >
                <span class="block text-blue-500 font-bold mb-1">Slides</span>
                <span class="text-xs text-text-muted italic">Presentations</span
                >
            </div>
            <div
                class="p-4 bg-bg-card border border-border-main rounded-xl text-center"
            >
                <span class="block text-blue-500 font-bold mb-1">Sheets</span>
                <span class="text-xs text-text-muted italic">Spreadsheets</span>
            </div>
            <div
                class="p-4 bg-bg-card border border-border-main rounded-xl text-center"
            >
                <span class="block text-blue-500 font-bold mb-1">Calendar</span>
                <span class="text-xs text-text-muted italic">Scheduling</span>
            </div>
        </div>

        <h3 id="oauth">OAuth 2.0 Configuration</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <strong>Consent Screen</strong>: Set User Type to <strong
                    >External</strong
                > and add your email to <strong>Test Users</strong>.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Credentials</strong>: Create an <strong
                    >OAuth Client ID</strong
                > for a <strong>Web Application</strong>.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Redirect URIs</strong>: Add <code
                    >http://localhost:8000/auth/google/callback</code
                >.
            </li>
        </ol>

        <h2 id="notion">Notion Integration</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>
                Create an integration at <a
                    href="https://www.notion.com/my-integrations"
                    target="_blank"
                    class="text-blue-500">Notion My Integrations</a
                >.
            </li>
            <li>Grant "Read", "Update", and "Insert" permissions.</li>
            <li>
                Connect your integration to your database via the "Connect to"
                menu in Notion.
            </li>
        </ol>

        <h2 id="environment">Environment Configuration</h2>
        <p>
            Create a <code>.env</code> file in your project root:
        </p>
        <pre><code>{`# Telegram
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN="your_token"
TELEGRAM_API_ID=12345
TELEGRAM_API_HASH="your_hash"
TELEGRAM_PHONE="+123456789"

# LLM Intelligence
GROQ_API_KEY="your_groq_key"

# Google OAuth
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID="your_google_id"
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET="your_google_secret"`}</code></pre>

        <h2 id="memory">Cognitive Memory</h2>
        <p>
            Gabay now features a <strong
                >20-message conversational buffer</strong
            >. This allows for deep context resolution:
        </p>
        <pre><code>"Research the history of Rome."
"Now email it to my boss." (Gabay knows "it" refers to the research)</code></pre>

        <h2 id="docs-quality">Professional Documentation</h2>
        <p>
            Gabay doesn't just dump text; it builds professional documents. Our <strong
                >Formatting Engine</strong
            > automatically converts raw intelligence into structured Google Docs:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <strong>Typography</strong>: Uses <em>Merriweather</em> and <em
                    >Montserrat</em
                > for professional reading.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Structure</strong>: Automatic centered titles, bolded
                subheadings, and native bullet lists.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Design</strong>: Professional spacing and logical
                hierarchy.
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="slides">Slides V3: Professional Engine</h2>
        <p>
            Our "Professional V3" engine creates cinematic presentations with:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <strong>Cinematic Layouts</strong>: Custom-built <em>BLANK</em> layouts
                for total design control.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Sleek Dark Mode</strong>: High-contrast, minimalist
                navy/black aesthetics.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Visual Accents</strong>: Dynamic accent lines and
                professional font pairings (Montserrat & Roboto).
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Native Bullets</strong>: Clean, structured lists for
                clarity.
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="recurring">Interval Scheduling</h2>
        <p>Handle high-frequency tasks with precision:</p>
        <pre><code>"Remind me to check the oven every minute for 5 times."</code></pre>
        <p>
            Gabay manages individual counts and seconds-based intervals
            autonomously.
        </p>

        <h2 id="research">Autonomous Research</h2>
        <p>
            Gabay performs web research and synthesizes findings into structured
            documents.
        </p>
        <pre><code>"Research AI agents and save to a doc"</code></pre>

        <h2 id="sharing">Sharing & Permissions</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Public</strong>: <code>"...make it public"</code></li>
            <li>
                <strong>Private Invite</strong>: <code
                    >"...invite user@gmail.com"</code
                >
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Roles</strong>: Choose <code>reader</code> or <code
                    >writer</code
                >.
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="commands">Command Reference</h2>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
            <table
                class="w-full text-left border-collapse my-8 transition-colors duration-300 min-w-[500px]"
            >
                <thead>
                    <tr class="border-b border-border-main text-text-main">
                        <th class="py-3 pr-4">Feature</th>
                        <th class="py-3">Example Command</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody class="text-text-muted text-sm">
                    <tr class="border-b border-border-main/50">
                        <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-blue-500">Docs</td>
                        <td class="py-3">"Create a doc about Q3 strategy"</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr class="border-b border-border-main/50">
                        <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-blue-500">Slides</td
                        >
                        <td class="py-3"
                            >"Make a professional deck about space"</td
                        >
                    </tr>
                    <tr class="border-b border-border-main/50">
                        <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-blue-500">Sheets</td
                        >
                        <td class="py-3"
                            >"Generate a spreadsheet of crypto trends"</td
                        >
                    </tr>
                    <tr class="border-b border-border-main/50">
                        <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-blue-500"
                            >Research</td
                        >
                        <td class="py-3"
                            >"Research global remote work impact"</td
                        >
                    </tr>
                    <tr class="border-b border-border-main/50">
                        <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-blue-500"
                            >Reminders</td
                        >
                        <td class="py-3">"Remind me every 30s for 10 times"</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </div>
    </article>
</DocsLayout>
